HEADWORD: Splashboard
<hw>Splash"board`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A guard in the
front part of vehicle, to prevent splashing by a mud or water from the
horse's heels; -- in the United States commonly called
<xex>dashboard</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Splasher</ent>⟦br⟧
